Ternary Operator
- Like a if-else-then but a shorter and efficient method

// dataType variableName = (condition) ? ifTrue : ifFalse;

Examples:

//In Calculation
double dailyWage = 500;

double taxRate = (dailyWage >= 700) ? (dailyWage * 0.05) : (dailyWage * 0.02);
System.out.print(taxRate);

Expected output: 10

//In Printing
int number = -4

String negativeOrPositive = (number > 0) ? "Positive Number" : "Negative Number";
System.out.print(negativeOrPostive);

Output: Negative Number

Substring Method
- A mathod used to extract a portion of a string

// String variable = variableThatIsString.substring(start, end);

Examples:

//Gmail Separator
String email = "exampleEmail@yahoo.com";

String domain = email.substring(email.indexOf("@") + 10;
String name = email.substring(0, email.indexOf("@");

System.out.println(domain);
System.out.println(name);

Output: yahoo.com
        exampleEmail

//First 5 letters
String name = "ABDCEF";

String firstFive = name.substring(0, 4);

System.out.print(firstFive);

Output: ABCDE


